the cost of FNA increased to $6,091. Dominance of the repeat FNA strategy was 
not sensitive to the cost of operation or the complication rate.
CONCLUSION: The NCI recommendations for repeat FNA regarding follow-up of 
AUS/FLUS results are cost-effective. Improving compliance with these guidelines 
should lead to less overall costs, greater quality of life, and fewer 
unnecessary operations.

