This paper summarizes the results obtained within the framework of the French 
PROMOTO Project (PROtection of the MOTOrcyclist). The aim of this project was to 
analyze the impact between a motorcycle and a light vehicle from an 
epidemiological, accidentological and biomechanical point of view. The results 
have made it possible to outline the most frequent accident configurations such 
as the "turn on the left" and the most common injuries sustained by motorized 
